    <node id="1. Recent changes in performance measures for English literature GCSE exams in Wales have had a positive impact on the number of students taking the exam, especially those entitled to free school meals.&#10;2. Previously, a performance measure around English was introduced which led to significant numbers of children, particularly those entitled to free school meals, not sitting for the English literature GCSE.&#10;3. This performance measure was changed last year, resulting in a significant increase in the number of children sitting for the English literature GCSE.&#10;4. The rationale behind these changes is that studying literature is essential for the development of literacy and oracy standards, introducing children to the joy of reading and the written word. It also helps in reducing the attainment gap between pupils who are eligible for free school meals and those who are not." />
