    <node id="1. The mixed picture of attainment across minority ethnic groups in Wales involves varying levels of performance. For instance, Black Welsh girls entitled to free school meals perform almost at the national average for all children, while Black Welsh boys do not. Similarly, White Welsh boys also underperform. This diverse performance highlights the need for a more nuanced understanding and targeted resources to address underachievement in specific areas (Speaker: Kirsty Williams AM).&#10;2. To address this issue, the Welsh government has committed to maintaining a ring-fenced grant of £10 million for local authorities to support the education of minority ethnic children. By having a more sophisticated conversation about attainment across different subgroups, resources can be better targeted and help in understanding the differences within the diverse minority ethnic group (Speaker: Kirsty Williams AM).&#10;3. This approach will ensure that efforts are focused on addressing the root causes of underachievement among certain subgroups, ultimately leading to more equitable education outcomes for all students." />
