rt of an effort to ensure that Estyn is not just making judgments but also being part of the solution for school improvement.&#10;4. Further adjustments: While continuous improvements have been made based on feedback, there is no explicit mention of specific ongoing plans for further adjustments to the school categorization system. The speakers mainly focus on how the system has evolved and its current state rather than future changes. They do mention that both the categorization system and Estyn inspections are evolving, but no specifics are provided.">
