    <edge source="50 percent of school funding has been directed towards professional learning for teaching staff. This investment has been driven by evidence on international best practices and what works in driving up educational standards. The speaker highlights that it is challenging to directly link the spending of a specific portion of the budget to particular outcomes, given the complexity of the education system. However, they believe that this investment in staff professional development has made a difference already and will continue to do so, as it aligns with what is known to work in improving educational standards." target="The Welsh government is taking several measures to address schools requiring significant improvement and special measures. A new multi-agency approach has been introduced to identify and support these schools earlier, focusing on three main elements: addressing fundamental issues within the school, evaluating the school's capacity for self-improvement, and providing additional support to the senior management team and governing body.&#10;&#10;This approach also aims to ensure sustainable improvement over time by shifting from short-term fixes to a more strategic, long-term plan. The government is working on developing better data analysis tools, such as monitoring staff sickness rates, to identify potential issues in schools earlier. They are also piloting this new multi-agency approach in two high schools within each local authority that have been identified as causes for concern.&#10;&#10;Furthermore, the government is encouraging local authorities to take a proactive approach to intervention and use their powers effectively. A national evaluation and improvement resource has been established to promote self-evaluation in schools, which has been underdeveloped in the Welsh education system according to various chief inspectors' reports. This resource aims to be practical and usable for schools, as it has been developed in collaboration with the OECD, middle tier, and practitioners.">
