oring staff sickness levels. High levels of staff sickness have been found to correlate with issues within a school.&#10;&#10;3. Targeted pilot program: A new pilot has been launched in which local authorities identify two high schools they are particularly worried about. A multi-agency approach is used to work with these schools and provide extra support, aiming to address the persistent challenge of moving individual secondary schools forward at a faster pace. This pilot program is being evaluated by Cardiff Metropolitan University and Swansea University to assess its effectiveness.&#10;&#10;4. Collaboration: The government has collaborated with organizations like the OECD, middle tier, and practitioners to develop practical and usable self-evaluation resources for schools, promoting self-evaluation in the Welsh education system as it has been underdeveloped according to various chief inspectors' reports. This is expected to improve schools' ability to handle and educate students who repeatedly struggle with GCSEs.">
