evolution efforts have resulted in fantastic documents but patchy implementation. The curriculum's significance and quality make it too important to be left to chance, requiring a relentless focus on successful implementation.&#10;&#10;In addition, the group will not disband after completing this task, as they have an ongoing role in overseeing the middle tier. This group operates at arm's length from the government, and while they do not report formally, they provide feedback to the Minister. The strategic delivery group is also considering a national service model with local accountability for monitoring and consistency purposes.&#10;&#10;As for the ERW (Education Through Regional Working) regional school improvement service, there are concerns about Neath Port Talbot's potential withdrawal from the consortium. While the Welsh Government does not intend to intervene directly, they seek clarification on Neath Port Talbot's plans to fulfill their functions in absence of ERW, especially considering the critical time for introducing the new curriculum. The government aims to ensure that schools and students are not disadvantaged without the support from ERW.">
