 Disadvantaged backgrounds: By analyzing capped 9 scores and other data sources, schools can better understand the performance of their free school meal (FSM) eligible students and work towards reducing the attainment gap between these learners and their peers.&#10;&#10;4. Curriculum choice: The new system encourages a more diverse curriculum choice to cater to the needs and interests of all students, rather than narrowing the curriculum to focus only on subjects that are traditionally associated with high performance in exams.&#10;&#10;5. Cohorts of children with different abilities: The new third-third-third system challenges schools to look beyond just the C/D boundaries and ensure that they are pushing more able and talented students while also supporting those for whom attending school daily is an achievement. This helps create a more balanced approach to student progress and success, regardless of their ability level.">
