s in the provided context) requiring significant improvement and special measures earlier. This approach focuses on addressing fundamental issues within the school, evaluating the school's capacity for self-improvement, and providing additional support to the senior management team and governing body.&#10;&#10;2. Difference from traditional methods: In traditional methods, Estyn would make a judgment on the school and then return for another inspection after a certain period (e.g., six months). However, under this new approach, Estyn is part of the solution rather than just making judgments. The multi-agency panel, which includes Estyn, works collaboratively with the school to support its improvement continuously, creating a more integrated and supportive environment for change.">
